Description: Handle of Knidian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp; club symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.173, 30. Names, Ierokles, Anaxandros. The KT number is 117, not 1177, as noted above. For the stamp see M. Palaczyk and E. Schoenenberger, Eretria XIII, 205, no. 78.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0307)
